<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-02-02T05:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-02-02T05:00:00-05:00" n="11" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d11">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">500.A15A4 Permanent Disarmament
                                Commission/89: Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The American Delegate</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Wilson</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Geneva</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-02-02T11:00:00+01:00">February 2, 1935—11 a.m.</date>
                                    <lb/> [Received February 2—8:22 a.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>971. Convocations have been issued for a meeting of the Committee on
                                Miscellaneous Provisions (Bourquin<note n="29" xml:id="d11fn29">Maurice Bourquin, Belgian delegate to the General Disarmament
                                    Conference.</note> Committee) to be held on February 18th. The
                                agenda consists of the examination of the questions referred to this
                                Committee by the Chinese Minister [<hi rend="italic">Conference
                                    Bureau?</hi>] on November 20th<note n="30" xml:id="d11fn30">
                                    <hi rend="italic">Preliminary Report on the Work of the
                                        Conference</hi> (Conf. D. 171 (1)), p. 137.</note> which
                                include the draft articles submitted by the American Delegation and
                                the Soviet proposal for a permanent peace conference.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Wilson</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>